Four people died and 10 sustained injuries after a taxi overturned on the N3 Balgowan near Pietermaritzburg on Monday.Ballgown N3 taxi crash leaves 4 dead 10 injured @ECR_Newswatch @WitnessKZN @News24 @_ArriveAlive @wordsfromshaun pic.twitter.com/XDH0MPZrCp&mdash; Netcare911 (@Netcare911_sa) January 9, 2017The taxi had rolled and come to a stop in the emergency lane of the highway.ER24 Spokesperson Russel Meiring said paramedics discovered that several people had been ejected from the vehicle when it rolled.&#8220;Paramedics assessed patients and found that four people, three women and a man, had sustained numerous injuries and showed no signs of life. Sadly, they were declared dead on the scene,&#8221; Meiring said.Eleven patients were found with injuries ranging from minor to critical and were transported to various hospitals for urgent treatment.Local authorities are investigating the incident.-TNA Reporter 